CHA CHA LARRY vied with another into the turn while in the two path, lost the lead in mid-turn, continued to chase the winner into the lane then weakened inside the eighth pole. GUN BUDDY saved ground through the turn and into the lane and moved up while not a serious threat. MR NEGATIVITY vied for the lead into the turn, settled back through late turn then tired through the final eighth. SHOWDOWN JUSTICE raced in the four path down the backstretch and into the turn when not far back, lost ground through late turn and into the lane and was empty after the eighth pole while in the five path. BIG CITY HEAT chased the pace from the two or three path through the turn then faded down the lane. ADAMANTLY CROSS raced in the five path into the far turn and was done in mid-turn.
